Oh, and minor third would be Eb, unless you are playing in B# :)]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It&#8217;s not actually breaking the rules. It&#8217;s applying a so called blue note. Say blues (and hence jazz, funk and fusion etc) are full of them. If you look at a blues scale you will notice that both major and minor third are int it :)</p>
<p>Oh, and minor third would be Eb, unless you are playing in B# :)</p>
